personalInfo.education: Clemson University (2009, Sports Management); Abilene Christian University

tourBios.exmtStatus: Fully Exempt: # Nearest 50 - 22nd Web.com Tour qualifier at 2012 PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.carHigh: 2012: Played in 21 events on the eGolf Professional Tour, making the cut in 10 of them. His best finish came at the NorthStone Open, where he T2. 2011: Won the El Jadida Classic in Morocco...Earned a spot in the Hassan II Golf Trophy on the European Tour. Missed the cut. 2010: Made his Web.com Tour debut, playing in the BMW Charity Pro-Am. Shot weekend rounds of 67-68 in his native South Carolina to T49.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won the 2006 and 2008 Monroe Invitational and the 2007 North and South Amateur. Reached the round of eight at the 2009 U.S. Amateur at Southern Hills in Tulsa. Won the Jay Haas Award for South Carolina Junior Golfer of the Year. College teammates at Clemson include touring pros Kyle Stanley, Ben Martin, Sam Saunders and Stephen Poole.

tourBios.carHigh: 2015: T10 at the California Qualifying Tournament shooting rounds of 74-70-72-73.
tourBios.personal: Hopes to play Augusta National someday...Dream foursome would include his dad, Mark Wahlberg and Jack Nicklaus...Twitter name is @phillipmollica.

dyn.dynBios: He's right handed but golf's left handed.
dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T49th in 2010 at the BMW Charity Pro-Am presented by SYNNEX Corporation.
